{"questionId":"20740","questionHtml":"<p>exactly one <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis intercept.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;will have one <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis intercept if</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>c</mi><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent reasoning)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>the minimum point is above the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award<em><strong> R1</strong></em> for a rigorous approach that does not (only) refer to sketched graphs.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>. The <em><strong>A1</strong></em> is independent of the <em><strong>R1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20740","referenceCode":"21M.3.AHL.TZ1.1e.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"exactly one x-axis intercept.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}